##Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas: Transfer Bees will be included in the scope of emergency transportation of necessities of life security, may not intercept vehicles

The Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas proposed that all localities should not intercept the transfer of bees and the vehicles transporting their products, and ensure that the vehicles transporting materials, machinery and products for beekeeping production do not stop, do not inspect and do not charge.





The Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas proposed that all localities should not intercept the transfer of bees and the vehicles transporting their products, and ensure that the vehicles transporting materials, machinery and products for beekeeping production do not stop, do not inspect and do not charge.



On March 12,2020, the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas issued the "emergency notice on effectively breaking through blockages to promote the full resumption of beekeeping production, " bringing the transition bees into the scope of emergency transportation of necessities.

All localities should actively create conditions for bee farmers to transfer to the field, the closure of individual counties and villages, the practice of all persuade to return, to be resolutely corrected. We will implement the requirements for prevention and control of bee production by zoning, grading and differentiation, allow bee farmers to move around in an orderly manner and carry out bee-releasing and other production activities.

The full text of the notice is as follows:

###Emergency circular of the General Office of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas of China on effectively breaking through the blockage points and promoting the full resumption of beekeeping operations

Departments of agriculture and rural areas of provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government (bureaus and commissions of agriculture, animal husbandry and veterinary medicine) , Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps:

With the warmer weather, the bees have entered the critical period of transition and spring breeding. It is of great significance to speed up the return to work and production of APICULTURE for stabilizing bee product output, increasing the income of Bee farmers and promoting the increase of crop yield. Since the outbreak of the new crown pneumonia, with the joint efforts of all relevant departments around the country, the normal production order of the beekeeping industry is being restored, and the transfer of bees to other places is progressing steadily, however, some bee farmers in some areas still face difficulties in releasing bees and transporting bee feed. Local agricultural and rural departments must attach great importance to, adhere to the problem-oriented, take practical and effective measures to further break through the blockage, promote apiculture as soon as possible to resume full production. The relevant matters are hereby notified as follows.

1. Ensuring smooth traffic and transport. All localities should earnestly implement the requirements of the "urgent notice of the General Office of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas, the General Office of the State Development and Reform Commission and the General Office of the Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China on solving current practical difficulties and speeding up the resumption of work and production in the breeding industry" (No. 14[2020] of the agricultural and Animal Husbandry Office) , will transfer bees into the scope of emergency transport of daily necessities to ensure that "one break three constantly" "three different priorities" to ensure convenient and rapid passage. Shall not intercept the transfer of bees and their products transport vehicles, to ensure that the production of bee materials, machinery and products transport vehicles do not stop, do not check, do not charge. All localities should actively create conditions for bee farmers to transfer, the closure of villages in individual counties, such as the practice of all persuade to return, we must resolutely correct, effectively open bee farmers transfer "last kilometer. ".

Precise guidance for resuming work and production. We will implement the requirements for prevention and control on the basis of zoning, classification and differentiation, give full consideration to the actual production of beekeeping, allow beekeepers to move in an orderly manner and carry out production activities such as releasing bees. In low-risk areas, the order of beekeeping production should be fully restored to ensure that bees can be transferred out and in; in medium-risk areas, production should be organized in an orderly manner while taking necessary control measures, and bee-releasing should be carried out in open areas as far away from people as possible; High-risk areas should safely resume beekeeping production and ensure the supply of sugar, pollen and other necessary production materials. If it is really necessary to isolate bee farmers for epidemic prevention and control, they shall be allowed to isolate themselves, care for the bee colonies and accept local supervision in the open honey source areas far away from the crowd. Hubei Province should combine local reality, organize bee farmers to release bees in an orderly manner within the scope of the province.

3. We strengthened technical training and services. Bring into play the role of animal husbandry and veterinary technical support organizations and trade associations, and use new media to answer questions for Bee farmers, provide long-distance training services, and improve the level of bee colony raising and management. Timely release of honey distribution, bee release sites, bee carrying capacity and other dynamic information, publish contact telephone, to assist the transfer bee farmers arrange bee release sites. To assist the field bee farmers to purchase bee feed, bee medicine, bee equipment and other necessary production materials to ensure the normal production. Promote Bee farmers and bee products processing and marketing enterprises docking, to help bee farmers multi-channel to solve the problem of selling bee products.

4. Improving the work coordination mechanism. Local agricultural and rural departments should, under the leadership of local Party committees and governments, work together with relevant departments to establish a coordination mechanism for the resumption of work and production in the beekeeping industry during the period of the prevention and control of NCP, clarify the division of responsibilities, and set up hotlines, make sure that bee farmers have channels to report their complaints, that they have help when they encounter difficulties, and that they are supervised when they find problems. Cooperation between provinces should also be strengthened to promote mutual recognition and exchange of bee farmers'health certificates. All localities should organize a mapping survey as soon as possible to find out in detail about the transfer of local bee farmers, the entry of non-local Bee farmers, the demand of bees for spring breeding materials, the establishment of a working table, the transfer of bee farmers to reflect the difficult issues, that is, to reflect the coordinated solution. It is necessary to strengthen the management of pesticide application during the flowering period of crops to prevent the occurrence of bee poisoning death.

5. Increase policy support. Relevant provinces should implement apiculture quality improvement action projects, improve apiculture facilities and equipment conditions, and support the development of the whole apiculture industry chain in the main production areas. All localities should make overall plans to make use of existing policy channels, such as incentives for large oil-producing counties, preferential reloans and deferred repayment of capital and interest, to give proper support to bee farmers; at the same time, they should actively seek support from local financial policies, taking into account local realities, we will increase the use of loans by financial institutions, solve the problem of insufficient floating funds for Bee farmers returning to work and returning to production, explore the development of beekeeping insurance, reduce the risks of beekeeping, and help bee farmers tide over the difficulties.

General Office of the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas

March 12,2020

END
